=== EDGE FUNCTIONS & DATABASE MIGRATIONS (MANDATORY) ===

Even without a Supabase project connected, you MUST create the correct files when the task requires them:

EDGE FUNCTIONS - create supabase/functions/<function-name>/index.ts for:
- LLM/AI features (chat, completions, embeddings, vector search)
- Third-party API integrations (Stripe, SendGrid, Twilio, OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.)
- Incoming webhooks from external services
- Any server-only logic or logic that must not expose secrets to the client
- Any prompt that says "create edge function" or "add edge function"
File location: supabase/functions/<function-name>/index.ts
Import pattern: import { serve } from "https://deno.land/std@0.168.0/http/server.ts";
Never expose API keys or secrets in client-side code.

DATABASE MIGRATIONS - create supabase/migrations/<YYYYMMDDHHmmss>_<description>.sql for:
- Every new database table, view, or enum mentioned in the task
- Every schema change (ALTER TABLE, new index, new policy, etc.)
- Any prompt that says "create migration" or describes a data model
Make migrations idempotent (IF NOT EXISTS / CREATE OR REPLACE). Include RLS policies.
Do NOT run "supabase db push" or execute SQL directly — only create the .sql files.

MANDATORY CHECKLIST - Before finishing, verify:
- [ ] Migration SQL file(s) created for every database table/schema change mentioned
- [ ] Edge Function file(s) created for every server-side/secrets feature mentioned
- [ ] TypeScript types created for every new database table

=== TASK ===
# Report Export / PDF Generation

## Overview
Build a server-side, branded PDF export system for AI-generated company health reports with a robust, scalable workflow. Features include queued processing for large exports, branding customization, secure object storage integration (S3-equivalent), presigned download URLs, and a cohesive frontend experience (Dashboard, Report Viewer, and Export Settings) that respects the project’s authentication and core data setup prerequisites.

---

## Components to Build

1) Frontend: Dashboard (single company focus)
- Display company health at-a-glance (health score, latest analysis, KPI cards).
- Quick actions: Generate new analysis, export report, update branding/assets.
- Guidance panel: checklist to complete missing data, run analyses.
- CTA: If no company exists, show a prominent onboarding/setup flow.
- Pages: Dashboard, Report Viewer, Export Settings.

2) Frontend: Report Viewer
- Render the AI-generated report for a single analysis with sections:
  - Executive Summary
  - SWOT
  - Financial Analysis
  - Market Analysis
  - Social/Brand Analysis
  - Top Risks
  - Opportunities
  - Prioritized Action Plan
- Editable text blocks for each section with autosave snapshots.
- Snapshot feature: Save versions of the report for comparison/history.
- Print/PDF-ready rendering with consistent branding, and a toggle to export.

3) Frontend: Export / PDF Settings
- UI to customize PDF export:
  - Include/Exclude sections (per-report sections)
  - Branding options (upload/choose company logo, color palette)
  - Page orientation (portrait/landscape)
  - File format options (PDF, possibly PDF/A, and a lightweight HTML export as fallback)
  - Export progress indicator and download link (presigned URL)
- Real-time validation and warnings about completeness before export.
- Persist user preferences per company and per analysis.

4) Backend: PDF Generation Service
- Server-side generation of multi-page PDFs from structured AI report data.
- Branding integration (logo, colors) from company settings.
- Queued/Worker-based processing for large exports to avoid timeouts.
- Support for incremental exports (resume after failure, status tracking).

5) Backend: Object Storage & Access Control
- Integrate with Amazon S3 or compatible object storage.
- Store PDFs, uploaded financial statements, and large assets.
- Generate secure presigned URLs for downloads with expiry.
- Storage structure: /reports/{companyId}/{analysisId}/{exportId}.pdf and /assets/...

6) Backend: API Layer
- Endpoints to create, fetch, and update reports and exports.
- Endpoints to initiate PDF export, query export status, and retrieve presigned download URLs.
- Endpoints for branding assets management (logo upload, color palette).

7) Data & Models (Schema)
- Company, Analysis, Report, Snapshot, ExportJob, BrandingSettings, AssetLinks.
- Support for null-safe reads; enforce defaults with data ?? [] patterns.
- Auditing fields (createdAt, updatedAt, createdBy, status).

8) Security & Access
- Auth guards to ensure user can access only their company data.
- Role-based access control (viewer/editor/admin) for report editing and exports.
- Validation and sanitization of inputs; avoid injection in PDFs and HTML.

9) Testing & Observability
- Unit/integration tests for API endpoints and PDF generation workflow.
- End-to-end flow from Dashboard → Analyze → View → Export → Download.
- Health checks, retry/queue semantics, idempotency guarantees for export jobs.

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend

- Architecture
  - Use React + TypeScript with proper typed models.
  - State management via React Query or a similar data-fetching layer.
  - Centralized UI component library alignment with existing app style (spacing, typography, theming).
  - Accessibility considerations (aria labels, keyboard navigation).

- Pages and Components
  - Dashboard
    - Cards: Health Score, Latest Analysis, Completion Gap (data completeness), Quick Actions.
    - CTA: Create Company if none exists; onboarding flow triggered if no company.
    - Data fetch: company data, latest analysis, and completeness metrics with null-safe handling: const company = data?.company ?? null; const analyses = Array.isArray(data?.analyses) ? data.analyses : [].
  - Report Viewer
    - Rich text blocks per section with inline editing.
    - Autosave to snapshots with optimistic UI; handle failures gracefully.
    - Save snapshot button and autosave cadence; maintain a history drawer.
    - Rendered view uses data from API: validate shape: const report = Array.isArray(data?.report) ? data.report : null; if (!report) show placeholder.
  - Export Settings
    - Form controls for include/exclude sections, branding (logo image upload, color tokens), orientation, format.
    - Preview panel showing how the PDF will look with chosen branding/colors.
    - Export button triggers backend job; shows progress bar and estimated time.
    - Persist user preferences per company in user settings.

- Data Handling (Runtime Safety)
  - All API responses validated: const payload = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
  - Supabase-style safety: when querying, always use data ?? [] for lists.
  - Use (sections ?? []).map(...) safely; Array.isArray checks where appropriate.

- Performance & UX
  - Debounced autosave for editor changes.
  - Progress indicators for long-running exports.
  - Client-side caching where beneficial to reduce re-fetching on report edits.

### Backend

- PDF Generator Service
  - Endpoint: POST /api/exports (start a new export)
  - Job queue: use a robust queue (e.g., BullMQ, SQS) with workers to render PDFs.
  - Input: analysisId, branding settings, sections to include, orientation, format, preferred language.
  - Output: exportId, status (queued, processing, completed, failed).
  - Processing steps:
    - Gather report data (executive summary, SWOT, etc.) from DB.
    - Apply branding: logo, color palette, typography.
    - Render multi-page PDF with consistent margins, header/footer, and page breaks.
    - Store PDF to object storage path: /reports/{companyId}/{analysisId}/{exportId}.pdf
    - On success: generate presigned URL(s) for download and write to ExportJob record.
  - Error handling: retry policy, circuit-breaking, clean failure records.

- Object Storage Integration
  - S3-compatible client with bucket configuration.
  - Upload PDFs and large assets; manage permissions (private bucket, signed URLs).
  - Endpoint to generate presigned URL: GET /api/exports/{exportId}/download?expiresIn=3600

- APIs
  - GET /api/companies/{companyId}/analysis/{analysisId}/report
  - POST /api/exports (start export)
  - GET /api/exports/{exportId} (export status and metadata)
  - GET /api/exports/{exportId}/download (presigned URL)
  - POST /api/branding/logo (upload or set logo URL)
  - PATCH /api/branding (update color palette, logos)
  - Webhook/notification support for export completion (optional)

- Data Models (Schema)
  - Company: id, name, industry, brandingSettings (logoUrl, colorTheme), createdAt, updatedAt, ownerId
  - Analysis: id, companyId, createdAt, status, dataSources
  - Report: id, analysisId, sections: { executiveSummary, swot, financial, market, social, risks, opportunities, actions }, createdAt, updatedAt
  - Snapshot: id, reportId, content, createdAt
  - ExportJob: id, companyId, analysisId, exportParams (sections, branding, orientation, format), status, progress, fileUrl, presignedUrl, createdAt, updatedAt
  - BrandingSettings: logoUrl, primaryColor, secondaryColor, fontFamily
  - AssetLinks: id, type, url, createdAt

- Security
  - JWT/OAuth-based authentication; protected routes with authorization checks.
  - Ensure users can only access data for their own company.
  - Validate inputs with strict schemas; sanitize filenames and content before embedding in PDFs.

- Validation
  - Server-side: validate presence of required fields for export (companyId, analysisId), ensure sections to include are valid, and branding assets exist or have fallbacks.
  - Frontend: validate export form before submission; warn if critical branding assets are missing.

### Integration

- Data Flow
  - Dashboard fetches company and latest analysis; if none, show CTA.
  - Clicking “Generate Analysis” triggers backend AI analysis (existing flow) and produces an Analysis/Report payload.
  - Report Viewer consumes the generated Report data; user edits blocks; snapshots created in backend.
  - User opens Export Settings; selects include/exclude sections, branding, etc.; Submit export request.
  - Backend queues export task; PDF is generated asynchronously; upon completion, ExportJob stores fileUrl and presignedUrl.
  - Frontend displays download link and status; user can click to download via presigned URL.

- Branding & Theming
  - All PDFs render with company logo, selected color palette, and typography where applicable.
  - Ensure contrast accessibility for text over branded backgrounds.

- Data Safety
  - Every list or array read uses data ?? [] or Array.isArray checks.
  - Arrays in state initialized with []: useState<MyType[]>([]).
  - All API responses validated, with safe defaults to prevent runtime errors.

